My sister and I decided to enjoy and support the outdoor dinning today when she took the liberty of moving her chair next to mine to talk in private. No one was next to us until an hour & a half later.Two people then sat next to our table and one specific table had the same set up but with 3 people instead and same distant. The manager approached my sister in a manner that was not warm at all to move the chair back to its original set up. Meanwhile this could of been addressed from the very beginning in a way by stating just in case anyone else comes we have to ask you to move back. But two hours later right before our lunch is over and ready to pay 79.00 with a bottle of wine and the guy next to us with only chicken wings and water for 15 dollars he decides to ruin our lunch and single her out. Just know if you have any issues whether it's food ,service or policy clarifications, Rest assure the current manager in that place has zero people skills and does not know how to Communicate with people. This review could be about so many things.  I could easily write a 5 star review about the food and there be no issues at all.  Because it is 5 star food, bright, colorful, amazing, flavorful bites of everything we had.  But the above all amazing thing about this place is it's individual service to each and every person in that establishment.  The attentiveness of our waiter was spot on from the get go.  He was right on top of us about drinks and making sure water was taken care of.  As if the service could not get any better, with the amazing food and great wait staff.  It was truly and I mean truly out done by the effort and attitude of whom I assume is either the owner or manager Greg.  He went above and beyond to make our dinner there, one of the best dinners I have ever had.  He came to our table to talk to us and ask about how we were doing.  Offered drink recommendations that were absolutely fantastic.  His attitude and charisma would single handedly get me to drive back from Buffalo to personally make sure I have dinner anytime I am in town.  Not only that, I will recommend him and this establishment to any of the many friends I have to either live in NYC or visit it frequently.  Kudos to everyone who works there, you have made a mark on a very special night.  Thank you!

The only thing I dislike about Campania is its proximity to my house and the never-ending temptation I have to fight to dine there.  Their pizza is beautiful (and by beautiful I mean perfect execution and down right delicious), the staff is ALWAYS friendly, and the ambiance is just right. I almost transcend into the 1950s and feel like I am in a movie (with the exception of the big flat screen TV on the wall).  We have gone as large as groups of twelve and as a couple and we have never been disappointed. They are doing a real justice to the neighborhood food scene and there should be more places like Campania in Bay Ridge.  MUST TRY: Foccacia, Lobster Ravioli, THE PIZZA! SKIP: Mac and Cheese (truffle). Bad execution, somewhat watery. Only item I’ve ever been displeased with.

This is definitely a 4 and 1/2 stars!  First off the restaurant looks great, I could see myself coming here quite often. The chandeliers and the big garage door style windows are a nice touch. Also a huge hats off to the fact they chill their glasses, all the cups come ice cold for your beverages. Classy touch for a pizzeria.  Next, the food! I think the chicken wings here were my favorite I have ever had. The wings were fried to a crazy crunch and dipped in buffalo/blue cheese sauce, it was unbelievable. The fried calamari was also cooked perfectly and very fresh. The meatballs were tasty as well but between any appetizer, i would get wings. Lastly the pizzas, we ordered the Lombarde, piccante and pesto. My favorite was the piccante probably because I like a spicy pizza and second would be the truffle masterpiece Lombarde, the pesto pie was a bit greasy so it was a little too heavy for more then a few bits.  Overall, I think it was a delicious dinner and I will definitely be back again.
